message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories as it proposes methods to improve the accuracy of automatic segmentation of rectal cancer in magnetic resonance images using deep learning. The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation, which is a common technique in machine learning. The paper is also likely to belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category as it proposes methods to improve the accuracy of a deep learning model. Additionally, the paper is related to medical imaging (cs.MED) as it focuses on the segmentation of rectal cancer in magnetic resonance images. Finally, the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NEURON) category as it uses deep learning techniques to improve the accuracy of segmentation.
